==Future==
On April 30, 2025, US Secretary of Defense [[Pete Hegseth]] ordered the Secretary of the Army to "end procurement of obsolete systems, and cancel or scale back ineffective or redundant programs, including manned aircraft, excess ground vehicles (e.g., HMMWV), and outdated UAVs".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://media.defense.gov/2025/May/01/2003702281/-1/-1/1/ARMY-TRANSFORMATION-AND-ACQUISITION-REFORM.PDF |title=MEMORANDUM FOR SENIOR PENTAGON LEADERSHIP |date=30 April 2025 |author=United States Secretary of Defense Pete Hegseth}}</ref> The Army said it would stop procuring Grey Eagles.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.defensedaily.com/hegseth-directs-army-scrap-outdated-systems-cuts-include-jltvs-ah-64ds-gray-eagles/army/ |title=Hegseth Directs Army Scrap ‘Outdated’ Systems, Cuts Include JLTVs, AH-64Ds, Gray Eagles |author=Matthew Beinart |date=May 1, 2025 |publisher=Defense Daily}}</ref>

